=========== Passives ==========
Damage Resistances: acid, fire, lightning, thunder; bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical weapons
Damage Immunities: cold, necrotic, poison
Condition Immunities: charmed, exhaustion, frightened, grappled, paralyzed, petrified, poisoned, prone, restrained
Ethereal Sight: The ghost can see 60 ft into the Ethereal Plane when it is on the Material Plane, and vice versa
Incorporeal Movement: The ghost can move through other creatures an objects as if they were difficult terrain. It takes 5 (1d10) force damage if it ends its turn inside an object
Etherealness: As an action, the ghost enters the Etheral Plane from the Material Plane, or vice versa. It is visible on the Material Plane while it is in the Border Ethereal, and vice versa, yet it can't affect or be affected by anything on the other plane
